'''Dónall Mac Giolla Easpaig''', [[Master of Arts|M.A.]], is the former Chief Placenames Officer in the Placenames Branch in the Department of Community, Equality and Gaeltacht Affairs (''An Roinn Gnóthaí Pobail, Comhionannais agus Gaeltachta'') in Ireland.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pobail.ie/en/PressReleases/Photographs/index.html |title=Department of Arts, Heritage and the Gaeltacht Website - Photographs |publisher=Pobail.ie |date= |accessdate=2011-10-03 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110927141550/http://www.pobail.ie/en/PressReleases/Photographs/index.html |archivedate=2011-09-27 |df= }}</ref><ref name="donegalcoco1">{{cite web|url=http://www.donegalcoco.ie/council/press/June+05/placenamespolicy.htm |title=Launch of Donegal Placenames Policy and Committee - Donegal County Council |publisher=Donegalcoco.ie |date=2005-06-17 |accessdate=2011-10-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.logainm.ie/en/inf/proj-mapping |title=Logainm.ie - Mapping|accessdate=2018-07-19}}</ref> He is a leading authority on Irish placenames.<ref name="donegalcoco1"/>
