The '''''Journal of the Siam Society''''' is an [[academic journal]] on [[Thai studies]] published in English by the [[Siam Society]].<ref>{{cite journal 
|author=|last1=Frankfurter |first1=O. |authorlink1=|last2= |first2= |authorlink2= |year=1904 |title=The Aims of the Society |journal=Journal of the Siam Society |volume=1 |issue= |page= |pages=1–6 |publisher=Siam Society |doi= |url=http://www.siamese-heritage.org/jsspdf/1904/JSS_001_0d_Frankfurter_AimsOfTheSociety.pdf |accessdate=March 17, 2013}}</ref> Established in 1904, it is the oldest academic journal published in Southeast Asia, has carried multiple influential works in the discourse of Thai history. In 2012, the journal and its entire collection of back issues were made available online with [[open access]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Siam Society journal now available to all |author= |url=http://www.bangkokpost.com/tech/computer/301595/siam-society-journal-now-available-to-all |format= |agency= |newspaper=[[Bangkok Post]] |date=9 July 2012 |accessdate=19 March 2013}}</ref>

